  m_Name: Pes_Distal_Phalanx_D2_L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Pes_Distal_Phalanx_D2_L
  partName: Pes Distal Phalanx D2 Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left distal phalanx of the second hind digit is the terminal skeletal segment
    supporting the claw within the canine hindpaw. It contributes to grip, traction,
    and stable toe positioning during locomotion and interaction with surfaces. Tendons
    attached to the distal phalanx control flexion and extension of the digit while
    maintaining proper hindpaw mechanics.
  - The bone also protects sensitive structures within the claw region and supports
    balanced force distribution during movement. Proper structural integrity is essential
    for coordinated gait and efficient locomotion. Injury, infection, or deformity
    affecting this phalanx may impair claw stability, reduce mobility, and compromise
    hindpaw function significantly in dogs.
